{"sections":[],"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components can be used for "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"layouts","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"anchor":"Colored-Surface","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Colored Surface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredsurface_Orange"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Mono","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" suffix (for instance "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"buttonColorBgDefaultEnabledMono"}]},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider"}]},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"anchor":"How-it-works","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"How it works"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the color, the "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsUseMonochrome"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsOnColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"How-to-use","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"How to use"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized)"]},{"anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Debuging contrast ratios"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", also named “RGAA”.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components like "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used on "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"]},{"anchor":"Divider","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Divider"},{"anchor":"How-it-works","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"How it works"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_horizontaldivider_Orange","type":"image"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"component_verticaldivider_Orange","type":"image"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSHorizontalDivider","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked vertivally (VStask)."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSVerticalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked Horizontally (HStask)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the "},{"code":"OUDSDividerColor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"How-to-use","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"How to use"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Layouts","modules":[{"name":"OUDSComponents"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"]}],"references":{"component_verticaldivider_Orange":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/OUDSComponents\/component_verticaldivider_Orange.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":"An horizontal divider in light and dark mode with Orange theme","identifier":"component_verticaldivider_Orange","type":"image"},"ic_folder_categories.svg":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/OUDSComponents\/ic_folder_categories.svg"}],"identifier":"ic_folder_categories.svg","alt":null},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSDividerColor":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsdividercolor","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"List of colors available for dividers (i.e. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSVerticalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"title":"OUDSDividerColor","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSDividerColor","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSDividerColor","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OU